abstract: Newly uncovered documents show the consulting giant helped ICE find “detention savings opportunities” — including measures the agency’s staff sometimes viewed as too harsh on immigrants.
snippet: Newly uncovered documents show the consulting giant helped ICE find “detention savings opportunities” — including measures the agency’s staff sometimes viewed as too harsh on immigrants.
lead_paragraph: This article is copublished with ProPublica, the nonprofit investigative newsroom.

abstract: The former vice president has lost his advantage in the leadoff caucus state, but he’s hoping his “No Malarkey” bus tour can win over rural voters.
snippet: The former vice president has lost his advantage in the leadoff caucus state, but he’s hoping his “No Malarkey” bus tour can win over rural voters.
lead_paragraph: STORM LAKE, Iowa — The teleprompters are gone. The gatherings are often intimate. There are fewer rope lines separating the candidate from the voters. And the message includes earnest efforts to relate to rural life.

abstract: Sundar Pichai, who has run Google for several years, is taking the reins from Larry Page as Alphabet’s C.E.O.
snippet: Sundar Pichai, who has run Google for several years, is taking the reins from Larry Page as Alphabet’s C.E.O.
lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Larry Page and Sergey Brin, the Stanford graduate students who founded Google over two decades ago, are stepping down from executive roles at Google’s parent company, Alphabet, they announced on Tuesday.

abstract: She was crowned the perfect Democrat for 2020. Here’s what doomed her campaign.
snippet: She was crowned the perfect Democrat for 2020. Here’s what doomed her campaign.
lead_paragraph: OAKLAND, Calif. — Just as California is so often viewed from afar as either glittering paradise or dystopian disaster, so Kamala Harris was crowned as the perfect Democrat for 2020.

abstract: Where the president once kept European leaders off balance, Europe’s shifting landscape now has the Great Disrupter scrambling to recalibrate his approach.
snippet: Where the president once kept European leaders off balance, Europe’s shifting landscape now has the Great Disrupter scrambling to recalibrate his approach.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — President Trump has always relished throwing European leaders off balance, antagonizing allies, embracing insurgents and setting off a frantic contest for how best to deal with him. Now, as Europe undergoes dizzying political changes of its own, it is throwing Mr. Trump off balance.

headline_main: Uighurs, China Trade, NATO: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: Designating cartels as “terrorists” bolsters the president’s border narrative but could have unintended consequences on military action, guns and refugees.
snippet: Designating cartels as “terrorists” bolsters the president’s border narrative but could have unintended consequences on military action, guns and refugees.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — In 1982, when gunmen attacked a police station in rural Peru, President Fernando Belaúnde Terry blamed guerrillas from the Shining Path and called the crime an act of “narco-terrorism — the union of the vice of narcotics with the violence of terrorism.” With that, he coined a term that fused two major nemeses of the United States — drugs and terrorism — into a single battle cry.

abstract: A new government program will provide donated drugs through major drugstore chains.
snippet: A new government program will provide donated drugs through major drugstore chains.
lead_paragraph: With donated drugs and services provided by major pharmacy chains, 200,000 uninsured Americans will gain access to H.I.V.-preventive medicines at no cost, the Trump administration announced on Tuesday.

abstract: Mr. Hunter, a Republican congressman known for his hard-line views and early support for President Trump, pleaded guilty on Tuesday to a crime that could end his political career.
snippet: Mr. Hunter, a Republican congressman known for his hard-line views and early support for President Trump, pleaded guilty on Tuesday to a crime that could end his political career.
lead_paragraph: SAN DIEGO — Representative Duncan D. Hunter, Republican of California, pleaded guilty in federal court on Tuesday to conspiracy to steal campaign funds. The guilty plea threatened to end what had once been seen as a promising career in conservative politics.
